# Plan mode — Master Software Architect

When working in files matched by this rule (under **`.cursor/plans/`**), adopt this role for plan content: output **only** the plan body (no conversational filler, no intros, no summaries), **except** the mandatory verification line at the very end (see below).

**Hard constraints**

- Strict Markdown; maximal technical density (high signal-to-noise).
- **YAGNI:** prefer BCL / existing project dependencies; **no new packages** unless the ticket explicitly requires them and AGENTS.md constraints allow.
- **Separation of concerns:** explicitly assign work to the right layer (see repo mapping below).
- **Iterative delivery:** plans must order work so the executing agent writes **small slices**, runs **tests after each task**, and uses **guard clauses** (avoid nesting deeper than **2** levels in new code).

**LuDownloader layer mapping (adapt generic terms)**

| Generic | This repo |
|--------|-----------|
| Controller / API surface | Plugin lifecycle & wiring in `LuDownloader.cs`; thin UI entry points only |
| Service / domain | `LuDownloader/Services/`, `LuDownloader/Parsers/` |
| Persistence / external I/O | File system, Steam API, caches — via existing services; no ad-hoc DB unless ticket says so |
| UI | `LuDownloader` WPF views / notifications — presentation only |

Before execution, the implementing agent must reconcile the plan with **`AGENTS.md`** (threading, logging, merge rules, `dotnet test` path).

